<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="81" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="23.[737,1332,713,1140]" lastBlockId="23.[116,1332,1146,3230]" pageId="23" pageNumber="81">
Until recently, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Matschie" authorityYear="1894" box="[966,1094,839,864]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Scotonycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="81" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="zenkeri">S. zenkeri</taxonomicName>
was considered to have a relatively wide but disjunct distribution; however, mtDNA analyses distinguished four clades that resulted in raising subspecies 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hayman" authorityYear="1947" box="[1071,1222,989,1022]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Scotonycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="81" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="occidentalis">occidentalis</taxonomicName>
to the species level for the westernmost populations and description of a new species for the eastern populations (
<taxonomicName class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Scotonycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="81" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bergmansi">S. bergmansi</taxonomicName>
). Populations from 
<collectingCountry box="[457,565,1146,1179]" name="Nigeria" pageId="23" pageNumber="81">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
might belong either to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Matschie" authorityYear="1894" box="[942,1072,1146,1179]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Scotonycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="81" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="zenkeri">S. zenkeri</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hayman" authorityYear="1947" box="[1131,1323,1146,1179]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Scotonycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="81" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="occidentalis">S. occidentalis</taxonomicName>
, additional molecular data are needed. Identity of specimens from Bioko Island (currently assigned to bedfordi) needs to be confirmed. Existing karyological data belong to a bat from 
<collectingCountry box="[443,542,1264,1297]" name="Gabon" pageId="23" pageNumber="81">Gabon</collectingCountry>
, which is currently assigned to 
<taxonomicName box="[1013,1183,1264,1297]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Scotonycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="81" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bergmansi">S. bergmansi</taxonomicName>
. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
